Title: Object: The beautiful Dromedary from Grand Cario [sic] in Egypt
Description: Camel standing, whole-length, in profile to left, two pyramids and traveller in the left background. 1757 Etching with drypoint
Curator's comments: See 1861,1012.2599 for comment. A dromedary is a one-humped camel whereas this most clearly is not.
